Package gov.anl.ipns.ViewTools.Panels.Contour

Class gov.anl.ipns.ViewTools.Panels.Contour.ContourJPanel extends CoordJPanel implements Serializable

Serialized Fields

LOG_TABLE_SIZE

int LOG_TABLE_SIZE
This is used to define the log scaler's source interval. The log scaler maps values from the interval [0, LOG_TABLE_SIZE].

NUM_POSITIVE_COLORS

int NUM_POSITIVE_COLORS
This is used to define the log scaler's destination interval. The log scaler maps from vaues to the interval [0, NUM_POSITIVE_COLORS}].

data2D

IVirtualArray2D data2D
Holds the data that is being drwn on this panel.

levels

Contours levels
Holds information which contours to draw (i.e. at which 'heights' will slices be taken from the surface and drawn as contours)

wcNotInit

boolean wcNotInit
Boolean flag that marks if the contour graph has had its world coordinates initialized yet or not.

Its initial value is 'true' and whenever the zoom is reset its value is reset to 'true' otherwise it is 'false'. The paint() method uses this value to determine if it should set the source (call setSource()) on the local transform (local_transform) (if 'true') or do nothing with the locl transform (if 'false').

Currently, this seems to be a way to get the contour graph to support both zooming and have the correct world coordinates set. However, there may be a better solution.

mainImageNotInit

boolean mainImageNotInit
Boolean flag that marks if the main contour plot has been drawn or not. This flag is used by the getThumbnail(int, int) method to determine how to generate the thumbnail. If this flag is true (i.e. if the main contour plot has not been drawn yet), the getThumbnail() method does not try to render a thumbnail and instead returns a blank image. This helps the startup performance of viewers like the ContourViewComponent.

logScaler

PseudoLogScaleUtil logScaler
Used to associate colors to contour levels. These colors are used when drawing the contour levels. The colors reflect the contours "height".

logScale

double logScale
Used to affect how the colors are mapped to contour levels. The closer this value is to 100, the more the colors are pulled to the high end of the color spectrum. The closer this value is to 0, the more the colors are pulled to the low end of the color spectrum.

thumbnail

java.awt.image.BufferedImage thumbnail
A reference to the thumbnail that refelcts the large contour image.

lineStyles

int[] lineStyles
Describes the line styles used to render the contour levels.

showLabels

boolean[] showLabels
Describes which contour levels are rendered with labels.

numSigFigs

int[] numSigFigs
Describes the number of significant figures each contour level's label is formatted to (and if there is even any formatting done).

colorScale

java.awt.Color[] colorScale
The array of colors that are referenced when determining which color to draw a contour line of a given height.
